        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 3:31PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Canada De Los Alamos, or 8 miles east of Santa Fe, moving north at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santa Fe, Eldorado At Santa Fe, Pecos, Hyde Memorial State Park,
Canada De Los Alamos, Tesuque, Glorieta, Tererro, Lamy and Cowles.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 63 between Mile Markers 5 and 25.
Highway 285 between Mile Markers 286 and 290.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 276 and 303.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
